Celtic's elimination from the Champions League on Tuesday night was celebrated by Legia Warsaw after they were controversially knocked out of the European competition.

The Polish outfit mocked Celtic over their 1-0 defeat against Maribor after they were thrown out of the competition for fielding a suspended player during the second leg of their 6-1 aggregate victory against the Scottish champions.

Legia Warsaw decided to appeal against Uefa's decision but did not have any success - which prompted the club to take their case to The Court of Arbitration (CAS).

