However their case was also rejected by the CAS which resulted in Legia Warsaw's bitterness towards Celtic.

Legia Warsaw chairman Dariusz Mioduski also decided to rub salt into Celtic's wounds by stating he thought 'the better team won'.

Celtic were on the verge of progressing to the next stage of the Champions League on away goals until Maribor captain Morales Tavares scored the only goal of the game in the 75th minute.

 

